{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"627b5501-d6c0-4608-b5bd-eed5fb58ecdb","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general recipe. Here's what to change:\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions Workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC trusted publishing):**\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # ← required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n      - run: dotnet build -c Release\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n        # No --api-key needed; the trusted publisher handles auth\n```\n\n### 2. NuGet.org Configuration\n\nOn **nuget.org**, configure a trusted publisher for your package:\n\n1. Go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers**\n2. Add a **GitHub Actions** publisher with:\n   - **Repository owner** — your GitHub org/user\n   - **Repository name** — the repo name\n   - **Workflow filename** — e.g. `publish.yml`\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag** or **environment**\n\n### 3. Cleanup\n\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**\n- Remove any `--api-key` flags from your `dotnet nuget push` commands\n\n### Key Points\n\n| Aspect | API Key | Trusted Publishing (OIDC) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Secret management | Manual rotation | No secrets needed |\n| Auth mechanism | Long-lived key | Short-lived OIDC token |\n| Scope | Whoever has the key | Pinned to repo + workflow |\n| Required permission | — | `id-token: write` |\n\nThe critical change is adding `permissions: id-token: write` and configuring the trusted publisher on nuget.org — after that, `dotnet nuget push` works without an API key.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a92d691e-643b-4a9e-81be-9cb845d9be31","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty with no workflow files. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":651,"requestId":"0410:32BB22:47BDB7:53B5DF:69F00561"},"id":"fa9c7d73-19c5-46f6-8b64-4954ed553196","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:10.005Z","parentId":"bc94f5a6-a45e-45d6-a1ac-003da63732d4"}
